docs.text: october sky is a rare oddity in cinema : a self-proclaimed " uplifting " film that is actually uplifting !
docs.label: positive

docs.text: based on the autobiographical book by homer hickam , rocket boys , october sky tells the struggle of four boys reaching for their dream .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's 1957 , and for the boys of coalwood , west virginia , there's not much hope of a rosy future .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: coalwood is a coal mining town , and , except for the few lucky ones who manage to escape on a football scholarship , most of coalwood's boys are destined to work in the mine .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but , in october 1957 , an event happens that sparks one boy to dream .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the launch of the soviet satellite sputnik sets homer hickam ( jake gyllenhaal ) to dream a future of rocketry and space travel .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of course , homer's parents ( chris cooper and natalie canderday ) aren't quite sure what to make of their son's unusual interests .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: homer gets his strongest encouragement from miss riley ( laura dern ) , a teacher in his school who also informs him about the scholarships offered to the winners of a national science fair .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and so , with stars in his eyes , and thoughts of scholarships in his head , homer enlists the help of three other boys ( william lee scott , chad lindberg and chris owen ) and begins to build a rocket .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but , do these four backwoods boys even have the slightest hope of escaping their destiny ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is a lot that could have gone wrong with october sky .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: nearly every sequence flirts with becoming syrupy and cliched .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , miraculously , october sky avoids nearly all of these pitfalls , making the exact right moves at the exact right times .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a film emerges which manages to be powerful and moving without slipping into the gauzy haze of nostalgia or sliding down the sugarry slope of sappiness .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jake gyllenhaal is outstanding as the kid at the center of this film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: >from the outset of the film , he is immediately likable , and never seems too corny or brainy as to alienate the audience .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: unfortunately , while october sky focuses on homer , the other three kids get the short end of the stick .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they remain little more than placeholders reading " insert friend here " .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of the adults in the film , chris cooper is the most fully realized character .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film never paints him as merely the villainous parent standing in the way of his child's dreams , but , instead , shows the multihued portrait of a man who wants the best for his family and town , but is too stubborn to realize what that is .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: director joe johnson deserves much credit for successfully navigating the many obstacles that october sky manages to dodge .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , there are still a few occasions when he allows things to proceed just a step too far .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: scenes which were natural and inspiring start to become contrived and artificial .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , these lapses are minimal , and johnson quickly steers the movie back on course .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the problem with many so-called " uplifting " films is that they attempt to force their mediciney goodness down your throat .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: october sky never resorts to that level , and yet , manages to become a truly uplifting film purely on its own merits .
docs.label: positive
